parameters:
Researcher Node: It may be a shabby place, but it's a
research facility. Sorry, but please let me focus on my
research.
Researcher Node: Oh, who are you guys?
Clea: I've checked the bulletin board.

Researcher Node: This is no joke! Are you really willing to
accept such a request for that amount of compensation!?
Clea: First, let me confirm the details of the request.

Researcher Node: My request is for you to collect as many
seashells as possible at Mucos and Beach Lepton.
Thief Nora: What are seashells used for anyway?

Researcher Node: Have you seen the village of Malaco and
the city of Bari?

Researcher Node: After the crystals stopped being
collected, the people of Bari became like the walking
dead.

Researcher Node: If you ask me... Bari was a place where
there were nothing but crystals.
Thief Nora: So, are seashells related to this somehow...?

Researcher Node: A woman named Armada is trying to change
the hearts of the people living in Bari.

Researcher Node: I believe that we need practical and
concrete measures, such as utilizing the abandoned tunnels
for cultivating plants.
Priestess Sophia: Is this... a medicinal herb?
Mage Relm: I haven't seen it either.

Researcher Node: It is a valuable medicinal herb that only
grows in dark places. I want to successfully cultivate it as
a stepping stone for the recovery of Bari.

Researcher Node: For that, we need a large amount of
fertilizer. In my opinion, seashells are the most
compatible!

Researcher Node: I can't offer a great reward... but I want
your cooperation!

Thief Nora: Y-Yes, let's cooperate! We've also been helped
by Armada-san.
Clea: I will accept the request.
Researcher Node: ...Thank you, thank you so much.

Researcher Node: Thank you for accepting the request that
cannot be settled with a small amount of money.
Clea: This is the seashell that was requested.

Researcher Node: So many of them...! What kind of magic did
they use!?

Researcher Node: Especially in Mucos, it should have been
difficult for thugs to easily gather seashells.
Clea: Those thugs cooperated with us.

Clea: They asked me to convey that they are supporting us,
the people from Valier.

Researcher Node: I've been conducting research for several
decades... I've always thought of it as a lonely battle.

Researcher Node: But even if they leave Valier, there are
people who still think of Valier.

Researcher Node: Thank you so much, you brought something
more than just seashells.

Clea: I don't mind going to collect more materials if they
are needed, even with the same fee.

Thief Nora: N-Nothing at all! I'm looking forward to going
to the beach again...

Researcher Node: It's not much, but here's the promised
reward. Also, please accept this prototype as a research
result.

Researcher Node: I thought it was a lonely battle, but it
seems that's not the case. Just that alone makes me want to
continue my research.
